                    <p>The Oi River gradually narrows until Kyoto's cityscape is displaced by a world of seasonal, ethereal colors. The Japanese word yugen --"immeasurable depth"-- is used to describe this kaleidoscopic display of verdant greens veiled by
                        mists, reds and yellows decorating the hills in the fall, and the white that blankets the scenery in the winter. There is elegance in this beautiful serenity.</p>
